This paper discusses the evolution of HTTP cookies and their impact on privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cyber law and policy (cs.CY). The paper also touches upon the technical specifications of cookies, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the political implications of cookies, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
